<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/Forum17/HTML/000028.html">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=0 WIDTH="95%"><TR ><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#F0DCA0" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Coes</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, I really want to run this game, but after about 5 to 10 moves, the game ends itself, and I am back in Windows.<P>System specs:<P>HD: MAXTOR 6L040J2 ( 32 GB free space )<BR>gc: NVIDIA GeForce 4 MX 440 with Detonator drivers WinXP 28.32 installed, but the installation did not improve anything.<BR>cpu: 1-AMD Athlon XP 1700+ dual bios, DDR, 256KB, mem 512 MB<BR>os: Windows XP Professional (5.1 - 2600)<P>I used the standard config options that came with the game. Glide rendering does not work, DirectDraw gives more problems ( only the sound of the game works ), the test works very well, and gives me 85 FPS.<P>Anybody can give me a suggestion?<P>I did install the patch as well! It gave me one big improvement: the game does not 'hang' anymore, at least that bug is fixed.<P>------------------<BR>allways supporting fellow countrymen</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Coes</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I did manage to get outside the first house ( took me 4 savegames ), but the game even crashes when I am outside, doing nothing but walking. It's not a 'pick-up-item' bug.<P>------------------<BR>allways supporting fellow countrymen</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alrik Fassbauer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hm, I don't know, but you could try the other possibilities in the Config Tool.<P>We have several complaints about Glide, but Lar said that the graphics engine is worked on. It should be ok in the full version.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Coes</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yes, I've tried all that too, but the problem is laying elsewhere I think. I can add this: I do not have that comp very long, but it was stable while running other programs/games so far.<P>------------------<BR>allways supporting fellow countrymen</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Moriendor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alrik: &gt;&gt;We have several complaints about Glide, but Lar said that the graphics engine is worked on. It should be ok in the full version.&lt;&lt;<P>Yes but most "complaints" were coming from people who tried to run the game in Glide on non-Voodoo chipsets. Glide does only work on 3Dfx Voodoo based gfx cards. No Voodoo - No Glide. It's that simple  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"> .<P>Some suggestions for solving your problem, Coes. I recently upgraded my OS from Win 98 SE to Win XP. Had no troubles at all with the demo on Win 98. Had a few problems with it on XP. It seems like the Detonator 28.32 has some issues when an application forces the gfx card to switch resolution (I have a GeForce4 Ti-4400). <BR>Try setting your desktop resolution to the game resolution, i.e. switch to 800x600 in 16-Bit color mode or if you've edited the config.div to play in 1024x768 change your desktop to 1024x768x16.<BR>Since your problem is related to moving your character you might also want to try changing your mouse settings by turning all Windows XP effects off. Search for the mouse settings in your control panel and turn off mouse pointer shadow, hot tracking effects and mouse pointer acceleration. <BR>If that does still not help, go to <A HREF="http://www.reactorcritical.com" TARGET=_blank>ReactorCritical</A> and download Detonator version 23.11. Uninstall 28.32, reboot and install the new (old) one. Det. 23.11 is reported to work very stable on Win XP systems.<BR>Last tip: use the program compatibility fix included with XP. It can be found in the program files\accessories folder or accessed via start menu -&gt; programs -&gt; accessories.<P><P>------------------<BR>Moriendor<BR>Editor @ <A HREF="http://www.rpgdot.com/" TARGET=_blank>RPGDot</A><BR>Webmaster @ <A HREF="http://www.planetdivinity.com" TARGET=_blank>PlanetDivinity.com</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Coes</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks for all your hints, Moriendor, but the game keeps exiting...<P>I did:<P>-install other drivers<BR>-disable mouse options<BR>-change the resolutions ( comp display & game config )<BR>-try the compbatibility-fix<P>nothing improved that exit-bug, in some occasions the game would not run at all. DivineDivinity looks great, but the demo is just not working for me.  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>------------------<BR>allways supporting fellow countrymen</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nemisis Dragon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Did you also try to change from 16Bit to 32Bit or 32Bit to 16Bit?</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Coes</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">no, but I have just been running Morrowind, and the crashing bugs are just the same. I have a conflict between Winblows XP and my video card ( -drivers ) or something it seems. Thanx anyway!<P>------------------<BR>allways supporting fellow countrymen</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alrik Fassbauer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Another possibility would be that the RAM-Chips are faulty, but only in those "high" areas, where a LOT of memory is used - and normally never.<P>You could change the RAM-Chips in their sockets, and look, what happens.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">RangGoon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Coes:<BR><I>no, but I have just been running Morrowind, and the crashing bugs are just the same. I have a conflict between Winblows XP and my video card ( -drivers ) or something it seems. Thanx anyway!<BR></I><HR></BLOCKQUOTE>At first I would try to use different graphics card. Perhaps you still have one from your older PC or can lend one from a friend.<P>RangGoon<P><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Coes</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">RangGoon, yes, I am going to try that. I hope it works. My comp only crashes -big time- while playing games, otherwise it runs without probs.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
